    "created_at": "2015-09-30T08:13:45Z",
    "updated_at": "2015-09-30T08:13:45Z",
    "body": "I\u2026 don\u2019t think there\u2019s an atomic way to ignore the umask in `open(2)`.\n\nBest thing you/we could do is calling `umask(2)` with `0`, creating the file and restoring the umask afterwards; but that pretty much circumvents the reason umask exists and exposes us to races (something we\u2019ve been trying to prevent).\n",
