    "updated_at": "2015-09-30T18:04:54Z",
    "body": "I agree with @nagisa that pairing together a `umask` call with an `open` call is probably something we don't want to do (e.g. the atomicity concerns), and it's something that could always be done by the caller.\n\nIs there, however, an API like `open` that ignores umask? If so it seems reasonable to bind it. If not then this is probably a \"working as intended\" sort of issue.\n",
    "author_association": "MEMBER",
